# AUTHORED-BY Claude Opus 4.8 (Fable unavailable) — re-review/upgrade candidate
#
@prefix fin:     <https://w3id.org/jeswr/sectors/finance#> .
@prefix core:    <https://w3id.org/jeswr/core#> .
@prefix owl:     <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix skos:    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .

# FIBO production IRIs (verified against the 2026-06-13 spec.edmcouncil.org snapshot).
@prefix fibo-fbc-pas-caa:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FBC/ProductsAndServices/ClientsAndAccounts/> .
@prefix fibo-fbc-fi-fi:    <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FBC/FinancialInstruments/FinancialInstruments/> .
@prefix fibo-fbc-fct-fse:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FBC/FunctionalEntities/FinancialServicesEntities/> .
@prefix fibo-fnd-acc-cur:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FND/Accounting/CurrencyAmount/> .
@prefix fibo-fnd-txn-txn:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FND/Transactions/Transactions/> .
@prefix fibo-fnd-rel-rel:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FND/Relations/Relations/> .
# FIBO modules for the v1.2.0 ledger + private-equity terms. IRIs byte-verified
# by the products (Keystone pod-store.ts, CapNote vocab.ts, both CONFIRMED-tagged):
#   LedgerAccount lives in FBC ClientsAndAccounts (fibo-fbc-pas-caa, above);
#   LedgerEntry lives in FND/TransactionsExt/REATransactions (a DIFFERENT module —
#   NOT ClientsAndAccounts); the private-equity fund lives in SEC/Funds/Funds.
@prefix fibo-fnd-txnsext-rea: <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FND/TransactionsExt/REATransactions/> .
@prefix fibo-sec-fund-fund:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/SEC/Funds/Funds/> .
@prefix fibo-sec-fund-civ:   <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/SEC/Funds/CollectiveInvestmentVehicles/> .
# ISO 20022 financial-messaging business concepts (UNIFI e-Repository).
@prefix iso20022:          <https://www.iso20022.org/standardsrepository/type/> .
@prefix schema:            <http://schema.org/> .

# =============================================================================
# Finance Sector Ontology — ALIGNMENTS (Mode A: annotation-only bridges)
#
# TWO REUSE SEAMS, kept apart on purpose:
#  - Mode B (real reuse, the default for FIBO terms whose AXIOMS we want): the
#    rdfs:subClassOf onto the FIBO slim MIREOT module lives in finance.ttl and is
#    reasoned over (F6/F7). It uses imports/fibo-slim.ttl, NOT whole FIBO.
#  - Mode A (this file, annotation-only): skos:closeMatch bridges to FIBO terms
#    NOT pulled into the slim module, and to ISO 20022 message concepts. NO
#    entailment — data authored against those standards is recognised without
#    inheriting their heavy axioms. The engine loads this only when cross-
#    vocabulary recognition is wanted; importing it never changes the reasoned
#    closure's consistency.
# Every line is a reviewable claim; nothing is silently inherited.
# =============================================================================

<https://w3id.org/jeswr/sectors/finance/alignments> a owl:Ontology ;
    dcterms:title "Solid Finance Sector Ontology — FIBO + ISO 20022 Mode-A alignments"@en ;
    owl:imports <https://w3id.org/jeswr/sectors/finance> ;
    rdfs:comment "Annotation-only (skos:closeMatch) bridges to FIBO terms outside the slim module and to ISO 20022. Mode-B FIBO reuse (subClassOf the slim module) is in finance.ttl. "@en .

# --- Accounts: subtype-level FIBO matches not carried by the slim module ---
fin:CurrentAccount       skos:closeMatch fibo-fbc-pas-caa:DepositAccount ;
                         skos:closeMatch iso20022:CashAccount .
fin:FinancialAccount     skos:closeMatch iso20022:CashAccount .

# --- Monetary amount + currency (FIBO match is Mode-B in finance.ttl; ISO 20022 here) ---
fin:MonetaryAmount       skos:closeMatch iso20022:ActiveCurrencyAndAmount .
fin:amount               skos:closeMatch fibo-fnd-acc-cur:hasAmount .
fin:currency             skos:closeMatch fibo-fnd-acc-cur:hasCurrency .

# --- Transactions & payments (FIBO FND Transactions; ISO 20022) ---
fin:Transaction          skos:closeMatch fibo-fnd-txn-txn:FinancialTransaction .
fin:Payment              skos:closeMatch fibo-fnd-txn-txn:Payment ;
                         skos:closeMatch iso20022:Payment .
fin:Transfer             skos:closeMatch iso20022:CreditTransfer .

# --- Instruments & holdings (FIBO match is Mode-B in finance.ttl; ISO 20022 here) ---
fin:Security             skos:closeMatch fibo-fbc-fi-fi:FinancialInstrument .
fin:Holding              skos:closeMatch fibo-fbc-fi-fi:FinancialInstrument ;
                         skos:closeMatch iso20022:FinancialInstrument .

# --- Account-holding role link (FIBO FND Relations isHeldBy) ---
# Core's account-holder mediation; annotation only — the Core mediation property
# is never widened.
core:hasAccountHolder    skos:closeMatch fibo-fnd-rel-rel:isHeldBy .

# --- v1.1.0 personal budgeting (Actual Budget) — schema.org Mode-A bridges ---
# schema.org has no envelope-budget term. fin:Budget is a PLAN information object,
# NOT a monetary value — so it is deliberately NOT aligned to schema:MonetaryAmount
# (that would conflate the plan with an amount and mislead semantic consumers).
# Only the allocation AMOUNT and the category taxonomy term get a schema bridge;
# the closest schema term for the per-envelope allocation value is schema:amount.
# Annotation only.
fin:allocated            skos:closeMatch schema:amount .
fin:categoryConcept      skos:closeMatch schema:category .

# --- v1.2.0 double-entry ledger (Keystone) — FIBO Mode-A bridges ---
# LedgerAccount ↔ FIBO ClientsAndAccounts LedgerAccount (CONFIRMED-resolving, byte-
# verified by Keystone). LedgerEntry ↔ FIBO's REATransactions LedgerEntry (the
# module where FIBO's LedgerEntry actually lives — NOT ClientsAndAccounts). Keystone
# dual-types its ledger resources with these FIBO classes; here they are annotation-
# only Mode-A bridges. The generic double-entry concepts FIBO has NO single simple
# term for (fin:EntrySide/Debit/Credit, fin:AccountClass, the account-code
# hierarchy, fin:JournalEntry) are deliberately UNbridged — no false FIBO IRI.
fin:LedgerAccount        skos:closeMatch fibo-fbc-pas-caa:LedgerAccount .
fin:LedgerEntry          skos:closeMatch fibo-fnd-txnsext-rea:LedgerEntry .

# --- v1.2.0 private equity (CapNote) — FIBO Mode-A bridges ---
# fin:Fund ↔ FIBO SEC/Funds PrivateEquityFund (CONFIRMED-resolving, byte-verified by
# CapNote — the dominant fund kind; fin:Fund is the broader vehicle, so closeMatch is
# an approximate anchor, not identity). fin:Notice's distribution case has only a WEAK
# FIBO analogue: FundsCashDistribution is a distribution POLICY/method, not a discrete
# call/distribution EVENT — so it is rdfs:seeAlso, never a closeMatch (CapNote's own
# honest treatment). fin:Commitment, fin:GeneralPartner, fin:LimitedPartner and
# fin:NoticeType have NO confirmed 1:1 FIBO class (CapNote kept them app-local for
# exactly this reason) — left UNbridged rather than assert a non-existent FIBO IRI.
fin:Fund                 skos:closeMatch fibo-sec-fund-fund:PrivateEquityFund .
fin:Notice               rdfs:seeAlso fibo-sec-fund-civ:FundsCashDistribution .
